runs.comm: terrific start by Pattinson, slips it really wide down the leg side, he would have needed three keepers to stop that
big inside edge and the ball rolls to the on side
goes back at the crease and knocks it to the on side
hits a good length on the off stump and he knocks it down to mid-off
that's a lovely flick, full delivery on the pads and he works his wrists and finds the big gap at midwicket
whacks it across the line and he finds fine leg, he wanted to hit more in front of square
Charles clears his front leg and clubs a length ball wide of square leg, big gap on the on side
gets forward and punches it hard but straight to mid-off
gives him a bit of width and Smith stands tall and thrashes it wide of point, sent the ball scorching to the boundary
tucks it towards mid-on and they pinch a single
Charles has faced only two balls and he already has ten! He makes room early, bends his knee to a full delivery and slices it high and long over deep backward point
just boundaries for Charles! Full delivery on the pads and he whips him away down to deep square leg
a touch wide outside the off stump and he slashes and misses
on target, length ball on the stumps and defended
punches it just past the bowler and they take a quick single
slower delivery and he adjusted his shot by angling it just wide of short third man
uses his wrists to whip a full delivery down to long-on, the fielder was pushed back
foxes him with a slower one, he was down the track and McKay did well to adjust his pace, swing and a miss
full outside off and he drives square, wide of point
pushes it quicker on the pads and he works it down to midwicket
swept but  just to the right of short fine leg
fires it flat and quick and he runs it down to short third man and Smith sends Charles back
swept but can't beat short fine leg
he chips down the track and swings just over the reach of mid-on who leaps sideways, but long-on's there to cut it off
opens the face and steers it down to short third man
premeditated from Charles as he walks across his stumps, fetches the ball from the off stump and swings him to deep square leg
attempted slower delivery but sprays it wide outside off
slower ball and Charles tries to slog but misses, the batsman isn't pleased with himself
another slower ball and he chops it down to cover point
streaky! Charles clears the front leg to slog a full toss but gets an inside edge that trickles past the stumps and beats short fine leg
pushes a slower ball to point and Charles thinks of a single
slogs at another slower ball wide outside off but misses
effortless drive! Full delivery outside off and he gets his body behind it and drives wide of cover
tucks it firmly down to deep square leg
Charles will be pleased he middled that better, on his knee and he swings and finds the gap at deep midwicket
goes back and slaps him down to long-off
Doherty drops it a fraction short again and he rocks back and thumps it between cover and extra cover
he makes the error by dropping short again, Smith rocks back and pounds it over midwicket
full on the off stump and driven down to long-off
slower delivery hits him on the pads but down the leg side, Watson appeals
high full toss turns into a beamer! Charles somehow manages to bend down and still slam it down to fine leg, Watson apologies immediately
drives a full delivery straight to extra cover
Charles tries to go downtown over the sight screen, makes room and it looked like there was a change of pace, couldn't clear long-off, Christian takes the catch
gets across and clips it towards midwicket and they do well to take the second run
good running again, Smith clips it wide of long-on and pushes Pollard for the second, puts pressure on the fielders
pacy delivery short and wide outside off and he decides to leave it alone
Lee aims for the body and he has Pollard weaving away from this short delivery and fending it off to the off side
full on the off stump and driven firmly down to mid-off
good length on the stumps and he whips it away down to fine leg and ensures he takes  a second
hammers a half volley down to long-off but the fielder from long-on mops up

that's a massive wicket for Australia,  Lee continues to keep it a bit short of a length and Pollard is cramped for room outside off, tries to dab it to third man but gets a faint outside edge to the keeper
that landed on the second tier! Can we have the ball back please? Picks a length delivery from the off stump and in one motion sends the ball soaring over wide long-on, tremendous bat speed
attempted yorker but wide down the leg side, fast yorker though
tries to run it to the on side, the ball skids through
speed of light! Smith picks another length delivery and carts it over wide long-on, didn't seem to put much effort but he sent that over the Sobers pavilion
wow! This was more exquisite, pitched up on middle and off and Smith merely lofts him over long-on, great balance and poise and that's his first T20 fifty
full on the pads and he clips it to the leg side
stays on the back foot and defends
slides down the leg side and he's punished for that, on his knee and sweeps wide of short fine leg
Smith has some lucrative deal with that on-side! Flighted and he gets on his knee and smacks it over deep midwicket
comes over the wicket and he fires it full, keeps him quiet
Smith goes for another big hit, he made room and tries to loft him over the sight-screen but turned the face of the bat and couldn;t time it, David Hussey takes it at long-on
gets well forward and defends to the off side
jams out a full delivery back to the bowler
gets well forward and drives a full delivery down to long-off
clips it towards long-on and there's a misfield by Watson in the in field
full outside the off stump and Pattinson does well to stop it at point
full and swinging in and he jams it back to the bowler
full outside off and he shapes to punch it straight but gets an outside edge to third man
full and wide outside off and he to Lee at sweeper cover
Watson keeps it tight, tucks him up for room and Sammy can only push it back to the bowler
slides down the leg side and wide called
drives to the off side very close to his pads and Watson thought it was pad first and appealed
tries to shovel a full delivery to the on side but can't beat midwicket
gets across and clips him to the on side
opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
misdirects the slower ball down the leg side
ends the over with a venomous yorker down the leg side and Sammy nearly lost his balance at the crease as he tried to dig it out

soft dismissal for Sammy, McKay bowls the slower one outside off, Sammy was at the crease trying to swing it away over the on side but ended up getting an inside edge that pegged back the middle stump
steers it to the off side, can't beat point
close call for Hyatt as he chipped a slower delivery over the on side but safe of long-on
Bravo was foxed by the slower one that was pitched a bit short and bounced a bit more than expected
clipped wide of midwicket and they push for the second run, good running
gets across and pushes a full delivery down to long-off
clips a full toss down to long-on and they take the first run quickly, good running again

Direct hit and the Australians look confident! It was clipped to wide long-on and Hyatt had to rush that second run, he managed to ground his bat just before the direct hit, I'm not sure who the thrower was, decision referred and he's safe, they took an extra run following the deflection
gets across and defends back to the bowler
an attempted yorker becomes a low full toss and Hyatt cracks that wide of extra cover. had to punish that
clips a full delivery to the on side to retain strike

the captain sets a good example! Hyatt doesn't pick a slower ball bowled from the back of the hand, makes room and sends the ball skywards, it swirls in the air for a long time and Bailey cupped it in the region of mid-off and went tumbling back
full and swinging in on the pads and he whips it behind square on the on side
drives off the front foot and just beats Bailey, long-off picks up
full outside off and jammed to the off side
bowls it full again and he pushes it down to long-off
slower ball and he reaches out a chops it towards point
West Indies losing the plot fast! Samuels makes a bit of room to a full delivery and mistimes the loft over the off side, the bat face turned and the ball was skied to Warner at wide long-off
tucks it down to deep midwicket
clips it with soft hands towards midwicket and takes a quick single
clips a full delivery wide of long-on and there was some hesitation for the second, Christian fumbled as the fielder hurled it to him and Baugh was in trouble
takes a single down to deep midwicket
nudges it down to short midwicket
opens the face of the bat and dabs it down to third man
makes room to slash outside the off stump and misses
should come as a relief to West Indies, Baugh gets on his knee and plays a forceful square drive past point and Lee had it covered near the rope but he too fumbled
fails to dig out a yorker outside off
slower ball on the pads and clipped to fine leg
full on the pads and clipped down to long-on
Bravo whips it straight to midwicket and Baugh was halfway down the pitch before he turned back, he had given up but the throw to the stumps was wide
slower delivery and he clips it down to midwicket
squirts out a fast yorker outside off to the off side
drives straight to extra cover and goes through with the single
Baugh backs away to smash that over the off side but gets a thick outside edge to the keeper, quite a soft dismissal, Lee pitched the ball up a bit
another wheel comes off, makes room to a length delivery and swings across the line, didn't get the timing or the elevation and finds Christian at long-on
lands outside the off stump and nearly gets a thin edge
gets across and punches it down to long-off
spoons it towards mid-off, not sure what he was trying
fetches it from outside off and swings it down to deep midwicket
goes back at the crease and slaps it to sweeper cover
Narine didn't see that slower one, it was pitched short and he uneasily weaved away from it
jams out a full delivery towards the right of mid-off and risk the single, there' s a direct hit by Bailey and Narine is yards short, looked obvious at first glance but the third umpire had a look
squeezes out a yorker towards the off side again and Bailey nearly effected another direct hit
West Indies fail to bat out the overs! Lee fires in an inswinging yorker on middle stump, too good for Edwards who makes room and misses, the bails are all over the place
